Package au.csiro.pathling.fhirpath.path

Class Literals

java.lang.Object
au.csiro.pathling.fhirpath.path.Literals
public class Literals extends Object
Utility class for creating and working with FHIRPath literal values.

This class provides factory methods for creating various types of literal values that can be used in FHIRPath expressions, such as strings, booleans, integers, decimals, and codings. It also includes methods for handling unsupported literal types.

    • numericLiteral

      public static Literals.LiteralPath numericLiteral(@Nonnull String literalValue)
      Creates a numeric literal value, determining whether it's an integer or decimal.

      This method attempts to parse the value as an integer first. If that fails, it creates a decimal literal instead.

      Parameters:
      literalValue - the numeric value as a string
      Returns:
      a new Literals.IntegerLiteral or Literals.DecimalLiteral instance

    • quantityLiteral

      public static Literals.LiteralPath quantityLiteral(@Nonnull String literalValue, @Nonnull String unit, boolean isUCUM)
      Creates a quantity literal value with a unit.

      Note: This operation delegates to either calendarDurationLiteral(java.lang.String) or ucumQuantityLiteral(java.lang.String), both of which are currently unsupported.

      Parameters:
      literalValue - the numeric value as a string
      unit - the unit of measurement
      isUCUM - whether the unit is a UCUM unit
      Returns:
      a new quantity literal instance
      Throws:
      UnsupportedOperationException - always, as quantity literals are not supported
